@user1:
This checks against the string "None" instead of checking against the [`None` constant](https://docs.python.org/3/library/constants.html#None) from Python. Instead, this should be something like:

```suggestion
        if val is None:
```

@author:
I did this because when I start qutebrowser using the command

`qutebrowser --temp-basedir -s qt.environ '{"QT_SCALE_FACTOR": None}`

for example I noticed that the literal None is never matched in this if statement however the string 'None' is so I assumed there was some sort of preprocessing that converts the None to 'None' before it got to this point in the code. Is this a problem or am I just misunderstanding how this is supposed to work?

@user1:
I think you'll get the expected behavior via `qutebrowser --temp-basedir -s qt.environ '{"QT_SCALE_FACTOR": null}'` (`null` rather than `None`), because YAML is used to parse config options from text. This certainly should be documented better, though.

